---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Commands Reference | CodeFi Docs">
  <div slot="header">
    <div class="text-neon-green font-mono text-sm mb-2">/ CLI REFERENCE</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Commands Overview</h1>
  </div>

  <p>CodeFi uses a highly intuitive command structure. Most commands follow the pattern <code>codefi [action] [options]</code>.</p>

  <h2>Playback Commands</h2>
  
  <h3><code>play</code></h3>
  <p>Standard playback command. Without flags, it resumes your last session.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>--mood [name]</code>: Play tracks matching a specific mood (focus, chill, synth, dark).</li>
    <li><code>--youtube [url]</code>: Play audio directly from a YouTube URL.</li>
    <li><code>--ai-mood</code>: Automatically detect mood based on current activity (Pro).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3><code>status</code></h3>
  <p>Shows the current track, artist, progress, and a mini terminal visualizer.</p>

  <h3><code>weather</code></h3>
  <p>Stay updated while you code. Shows current conditions and a 3-day forecast.</p>
  <pre><code>$ codefi weather "New York"</code></pre>

  <h3><code>lyrics</code></h3>
  <p>Fetches lyrics for the current track via Genius API. Supports static search as well.</p>
  <pre><code>$ codefi lyrics "Lofi Study" --artist "CodeFi Beats"</code></pre>

  <h2>Library Management</h2>

  <h3><code>history</code></h3>
  <p>View your top tracks and recent session history.</p>
  <pre><code>$ codefi history --stats</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playlist</code></h3>
  <p>Interact with your personal collections.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>list</code>: Show all available playlists.</li>
    <li><code>create [name]</code>: Initialize a new collection (Pro).</li>
    <li><code>play [name]</code>: Start playback from a specific playlist.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Productivity Tools</h2>

  <h3><code>focus</code></h3>
  <p>Enter deep focus mode. This is the ultimate tool for deep work.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Enables <strong>Do Not Disturb</strong> system-wide.</li>
    <li>Blocks distracting websites (Facebook, Twitter, Reddit, etc.) via <code>/etc/hosts</code>.</li>
    <li>Automatically plays your preferred focus music.</li>
  </ul>
  <pre><code>$ codefi focus start 60</code></pre>

  <h3><code>timer</code></h3>
  <p>Track your total keyboard time. Helps you visualize your productivity trends.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>today</code>: Detailed bar chart of today's coding sessions.</li>
    <li><code>week</code>: Weekly summary and daily breakdown.</li>
    <li><code>reset</code>: Clear your history.</li>
  </ul>
  <pre><code>$ codefi timer start --note "Building landing page"</code></pre>

  <h3><code>pomodoro</code></h3>
  <p>Control the integrated Pomodoro timer (Pro).</p>
  <pre><code>$ codefi pomodoro start</code></pre>
  <p><strong>Note:</strong> During a break, CodeFi will automatically dim or pause the music depending on your configuration.</p>

</DocsLayout>
